  skullRemark: "Huh, karma got him good."
  luciferRemark: "What's that phrase? 'Acceptable business risk'?\r\n\r\n(Pause.)\r\n\r\nHe knew. He always knew. Every expired extinguisher, every dead battery, every blocked exit - he knew exactly what he was doing.\r\n\r\nBut it was never his fault, was it? The corporation wouldn't pay. The tenants didn't complain. The inspector could be ignored.\r\n\r\n(Soft laugh.)\r\n\r\nSomeone pushed him on the stairs. How very appropriate."
